race.comment: FANTASTIC RALPH (2) finished in the placings last time but could not have been more impressive three back in his convincing 22.29 win at Maitland over 400m. Can return to winning form here if runs up to best figures. SALAMAT (1) held her own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only half a length (20.12) behind Denawen Beach at this track. Has never missed the frame from six starts from this draw, including two wins. Hard to beat again. MORTAR (4) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by a nose at this track in a handy 19.87 beating Sweet Bevely Ann. Boasts three wins from four starts out of this box. Should feature again. JOE CARGO (6) hit the frame here last start and can sneak into the finish again.
